<section id="course-maps-across-multiple-videos" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="course-maps-across-multiple-videos">Course maps across multiple videos</h2>
<p>Once several videos in a course are cached, <code>yttoc-map</code> builds a single Markdown learning map with three views — <strong>By Lecture</strong> / <strong>By Topic</strong> / <strong>By Keyword</strong> — each section linking to the YouTube player at the right timestamp.</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb7" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb7-1"><span class="ex" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">yttoc-map</span> <span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">$(</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">cat</span> course-ids.txt<span class="va" style="color: #111111;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">)</span> <span class="at" style="color: #657422;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">--title</span> <span class="st" style="color: #20794D;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">"My Course Map"</span> <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">&gt;</span> course-map.md</span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Render it as an interactive folding mindmap (single offline HTML file):</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb8" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode bash code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode bash"><span id="cb8-1"><span class="ex" style="color: null;
